{61932=PHILADELPHIA (Ticker) -- Walter Washington passed for 222 
yards, rushed for 119 more and accounted for three touchdowns as
Temple won its first game of the season, 38-7, over Division
I-AA Florida A&M.

With the score tied, 7-7, Washington began a string of 31
unanswered points with a 10-yard TD run with 5:42 to go in the
opening quarter.

After Ryan Lux added a 35-yard field goal late in the first,
Washington capped an 18-play, 98-yard drive with a five-yard TD
run to give the Owls a 24-7 lead that they took into the half.
It is the third straight game that the senior quarterback has
rushed for two scores.

The Rattlers were marching after receiving the opening kick of
the second half, but their 10-play drive was thwarted when
cornerback Ray Lamb recovered a fumble at the Temple 33.

Temple (1-2) took advantage of the turnover as Washington threw
his first TD pass of the season, a 17-yard strike to Ikey Chuku,
who caught five passes for 115 yards.

Umar Ferguson finished off Florida A&M (0-3) by capping a
15-play, 94-yard drive with a one-yard plunge late in the
fourth.  Ferguson rushed for a season-high 118 yards on 25
carries, his first 100-yard game of the season.}
